               <p>- Ashwood deposed, that he followed the prisoner; that he found him with the money in his hand; that he secured his hand and took him back to the prosecutor's house; that there the money was poured out into Mrs. Jordain's lap, and Stoddard picked out a remarkable shilling, which was produced and deposed to by him in Court.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I leave myself to the mercy of the Court.</p>
